      <bioghist id="aspace_3705191ded8e068038b11f4490916bf6">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Miriam Jaffe graduated from Yale College in 1982. She was active in feminist and gay and lesbian organizations at Yale, including the YaLesbians and the Gay Student Center, and in New Haven's lesbian and gay community. Jaffe produced parties under the name MJ Productions that were popular among gay men and lesbians on campus.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_5c119041d4c5db352d2e82ef2f5db61a">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers document Miriam Jaffe's participation in gay and lesbian student life at Yale and in New Haven, as well as her party production company, MJ Productions. The papers consist of advertisements, event calendars, programs, newsletters and playbills.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_93332a571963bd636c8a28fa4123d8f5">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged alphabetically by organization name.</p>  
      </arrangement>
